1
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:17,533
- What are you doing here?
- I saw you with Yenyen earlier.

2
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,567
Whatever is going on
between Yenyen and me

3
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:20,767
has nothing to do with you.

4
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,467
- Stay out of it.
- If she's the girl

5
00:00:22,533 --> 00:00:24,400
that you like, then so be it.

6
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:25,800
I'm not against it.

7
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:27,567
- What?
- Now tell me,

8
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:31,200
what is so special
about this Yenyen girl?

9
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:36,367
Don't hesitate to tell me
your secrets or your feelings.

10
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:38,467
How she helped me
when we were on the island.

11
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:40,067
But why do I feel that...

12
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:41,600
You were wrong.

13
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,333
It's Saturday.
Where are you going?

14
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,267
Raichu asked me
to come with her.

15
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,833
She needs to get swimwear.

16
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,500
Sir, follow that taxi.

17
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:50,233
Auntie, I'm at this restaurant
right now.

18
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,300
And guess what?

19
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,600
Red is here too.

20
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:55,567
I want to meet Yenyen.

21
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:56,600
Miss!

22
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:59,367
Do you know where Cafe Polca is?

23
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:01,533
- Just go straight that way.
- Okay, thank you.

24
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,967
I was right.
Red and Yenyen are here.

25
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,033
Fantastic!

26
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:06,367
Well, there she is!

27
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:09,300
I'm finally going to meet
Red's girlfriend.

28
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,367
Red.

29
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:12,633
Mom, what are you doing here?

30
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:14,400
I'm here to meet Yenyen.

31
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:17,300
Eden?

32
00:01:17,367 --> 00:01:20,367
- Your mother murdered my son!
- Mom!

33
00:01:20,433 --> 00:01:21,600
Mom, don't hurt Yenyen.

34
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:23,433
Get out of here!

35
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,633
Why are you hurting my daughter?

36
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,967
Get her away from my son!

37
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:28,900
Red is my boyfriend, Mom.

38
00:01:28,967 --> 00:01:31,533
Me and Yenyen love each other!

39
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,467
I don't wanna hear this anymore,
Red!

40
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:35,233
Let's go home! Stop this!

41
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,400
This is enough!

42
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:41,967
- Mom.
- Take back what you said.

43
00:01:42,067 --> 00:01:43,767
Take it back.

44
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:45,467
Take it back, Eden!

45
00:01:45,533 --> 00:01:46,667
Take back what you said.

46
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:48,300
That's not true!

47
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:49,833
I'm sorry, Mom.

48
00:01:51,567 --> 00:01:53,567
I'm sorry.

49
00:01:53,633 --> 00:01:56,800
Have you already forgotten
what they did to us?

50
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,733
I went to jail
because of that family!

51
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,733
They ruined my life.

52
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:04,600
You should hate them too!

53
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:09,767
Because they made my life
a living hell!

54
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:11,467
And now...

55
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:15,433
And now you're telling me
that you love him!

56
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,467
I'm sorry, Mom.

57
00:02:18,533 --> 00:02:20,000
I'm sorry.

58
00:02:20,067 --> 00:02:22,500
- I didn't mean it.
- Sorry?

59
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:24,533
You're saying that you're sorry?

60
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:29,433
Do you know
how much you hurt me?

61
00:02:30,867 --> 00:02:31,933
You should have just hit me!

62
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,433
Because physical pain
will eventually go away!

63
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,767
But this...

64
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:43,100
To say that you love
the son of that witch

65
00:02:43,167 --> 00:02:46,700
who made me suffer...

66
00:02:46,767 --> 00:02:50,000
You will hurt me
for the rest of my life!

67
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:53,300
I didn't mean to hurt you, Mom.

68
00:02:53,367 --> 00:02:55,567
We met on the island.

69
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:58,067
Red is a good person.

70
00:02:58,133 --> 00:02:59,967
He helped me survive.

71
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:03,900
Didn't I tell you
about how I owe him my life?

72
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:04,967
I couldn't take this,

73
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:06,233
even if you say
you didn't mean to fall for him.

74
00:03:07,267 --> 00:03:10,633
- Mom, please believe me.
- I can't take this!

75
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:12,467
Mom, believe me.

76
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:15,533
I didn't know
that he was Rina's son.

77
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:18,067
Mom, I'm sorry.

78
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:19,267
I'm sorry.

79
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:23,167
I don't care even if you tell me
you owe him your life.

80
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:26,333
Because his mom owes me
more than that!

81
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,567
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

82
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:28,633
Do you understand me?

83
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,633
You don't owe them anything!

84
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:33,000
They owe us!

85
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:35,933
I'm sorry, Mom.

86
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,433
Come on.

87
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,167
We'll live in the province.

88
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:44,900
So you'll never see him again!

89
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,600
Mom, no!

90
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:47,633
We'll live in the province!

91
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,933
- No, Mom!
- Let's go!

92
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,467
- Yenyen!
 - Red! Red!

93
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:52,333
- Where are you going?
- Yen!

94
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,767
- Red! Red!
- Don't touch her!

95
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:56,100
- Let go of her!
- Yenyen, I'm sorry.

96
00:03:56,167 --> 00:03:57,500
Yenyen...

97
00:03:57,567 --> 00:03:58,867
- Don't touch my daughter!
- Yen, sorry.

98
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:01,233
- Don't touch my daughter!
- We love each other!

99
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:02,900
What?

100
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,533
- What are you talking about?
- Yen!

101
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,633
What love are you talking about?

102
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:10,267
- Don't you dare!
- Your family did me wrong!

103
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,200
You're a bunch of pests!

104
00:04:12,267 --> 00:04:13,800
Pests! That's what you are!

105
00:04:13,867 --> 00:04:15,667
- Pests!
- Mom, stop it!

106
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:17,233
I will never forgive you!

107
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:22,633
So forget about the love
you have for my daughter!

108
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,300
Because I will never forgive
your family!

109
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:25,733
It's all your daughter's fault!

110
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,533
- Shut up!
- She seduced my son!

111
00:04:27,633 --> 00:04:29,367
Mom! Stop!

112
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:30,933
You're the pest!

113
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:31,933
Mom, stop!

114
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,033
- That's enough!
- Murderer!

115
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,167
Pest!

116
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:37,000
Leave us alone!

117
00:04:37,067 --> 00:04:38,333
Mom! Mom!

118
00:04:39,767 --> 00:04:41,567
Mom, stop!

119
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:43,767
- Mom!
- You're not going to stop!

120
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,133
Come here!

121
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,500
I'm not done with you!

122
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:48,500
Mom, stop! Yen!

123
00:04:48,567 --> 00:04:49,733
Let go of me!

124
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,967
- Come here!
- Mom!

125
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:57,500
- This is what you deserve!
- Mom, stop!

126
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:00,400
Mom, please stop! Stop!
Please stop!

127
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,733
That hurts!

128
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:04,833
Mom, stop!

129
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:11,000
You're a monster, Amanda!

130
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:13,133
You tore my branded clothes!

131
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,300
Mom, please stop!

132
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,200
- Mom, stop!
- You're a monster!

133
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:21,700
Your and your promiscuous
daughter's life

134
00:05:21,767 --> 00:05:25,667
are not enough to pay
for what you owe us!

135
00:05:25,733 --> 00:05:27,967
I don't owe you anything!

136
00:05:28,033 --> 00:05:29,567
Because you're the one
who did me wrong!

137
00:05:29,633 --> 00:05:32,167
You owe me a lot!

138
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:33,300
Mom!

139
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:35,633
And tell your son to stay away
from my daughter!

140
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:38,567
Because I will never let her

141
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:43,767
have a relationship
with a demon!

142
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:45,167
- And we don't want...
- Mom, stop it!

143
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:46,733
to be around criminals!

144
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,133
We don't like criminals!

145
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,600
Look at that woman!

146
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:50,600
- That's her mom!
- Mom!

147
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,233
- I know! Stop!
- Do you want to be...

148
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:53,700
Mom, please, stop!

149
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:55,233
What else would you like me
to break?

150
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,467
Murderer!

151
00:05:56,533 --> 00:06:00,167
Do you want me
to ruin your face?

152
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,433
Mom, this is embarrassing!
Don't do this here.

153
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,933
You can't be with her!

154
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,367
Not her!
She's a criminal's daughter!

155
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:08,733
A criminal's daughter!

156
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,133
You're both garbage!

157
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,533
Stay away from her, Son.

158
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,000
-You have to stay away from her!
-Mom, please.

159
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:22,900
Come on.

160
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:29,133
- My bag! Get my bag!
- Let's go.

161
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,167
Mom!

162
00:06:43,233 --> 00:06:46,100
Mom! Mom, let me tend
to your wound.

163
00:06:48,967 --> 00:06:51,467
Why won't you tend
to my broken heart first?

164
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,767
You've already forgotten
what they did.

165
00:06:56,067 --> 00:07:00,267
Do you really have
to fall in love with Rina's son?

166
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:05,467
You know what they did to me,
right?

167
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:08,900
How can you love Red
after all that?

168
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:11,867
How?

169
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,167
Mom, he's a good person.

170
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,567
He's not like his mom.

171
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:19,600
I don't care!

172
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:23,467
Do you think you'll have
a decent life with them?

173
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,933
Red, where are you going?

174
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,433
Where are you going?

175
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,567
I need to go see, Yenyen.

176
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:36,400
Her mom might hurt her.

177
00:07:36,467 --> 00:07:38,033
Red, stay out of their business.

178
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:40,533
Please. They can kill each other
for all I care.

179
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:43,567
They're garbage, anyway!

180
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:46,667
It's my fault
that her mom is mad at her.

181
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:48,500
It is not your fault.

182
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,333
She seduced you
while you were on the island.

183
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:54,533
Okay, you were vulnerable,
so she took advantage!

184
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,967
It will pass, Son.

185
00:07:56,033 --> 00:07:56,967
You will forget about her.

186
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,633
- All of this will pass.
- Of course not!

187
00:07:59,667 --> 00:08:00,833
Mom, I love Yenyen.

188
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:03,000
What I feel for her is real.

189
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:04,867
Sorry, but I can't do
what you want.

190
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:07,167
Red... Red.

191
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:08,333
Red, come back!

192
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:10,900
Red!

193
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:11,967
Red...

194
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,167
Ouch...

195
00:08:17,367 --> 00:08:18,333
Ouch!

196
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,933
- Mom.
- My chest hurts.

197
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:23,033
Mom!

198
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:25,067
- Dad! Mom, are you okay?
- It hurts.

199
00:08:25,133 --> 00:08:26,433
-What happened?
-We'll take you to the hospital.

200
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,467
What happened?

201
00:08:27,533 --> 00:08:28,833
My chest hurts!

202
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,933
Maybe we should bring her
to the hospital.

203
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,100
- Rina, are you okay?
- It's your son's fault.

204
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:36,567
What are you doing here?
I thought you were leaving.

205
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:38,667
Go! Go ahead, leave!

206
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:44,033
I won't leave you, Mom.
I'll stay here.

207
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,767
I'm sorry.

208
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,200
Okay?

209
00:08:47,267 --> 00:08:49,467
Are you okay?
Are you feeling better?

210
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:50,467
What?
Why won't you answer me?

211
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:57,733
You know what the answer is!

212
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,967
It's hell!

213
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:05,000
Rina won't leave you alone!

214
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:07,167
She will take it out on you!

215
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:08,700
Because we're enemies.

216
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:14,667
She will forever make you pay
for something I didn't do!

217
00:09:14,733 --> 00:09:17,400
I know that, Mom.

218
00:09:17,467 --> 00:09:21,100
I broke up with him
when I found out the truth.

219
00:09:22,633 --> 00:09:24,467
But I love him.

220
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:31,333
And Red doesn't believe
you had something to do

221
00:09:31,433 --> 00:09:33,333
with his brother's death.

222
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:37,500
No matter what you say,
it won't change my mind.

223
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:39,667
I don't like Red for you.

224
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:40,867
Forget he ever exists!

225
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:45,000
Or you can forget that I exist!

226
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:22,367
She doesn't want me to take her
to the hospital.

227
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:25,367
She said
she just needed some rest.

228
00:10:26,467 --> 00:10:27,500
She said she was fine.

229
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:34,200
Dad, I don't intend to hurt her.

230
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,100
Yeah, I know.

231
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:40,300
She told me about Eden.

232
00:10:40,367 --> 00:10:42,767
And it also hurts to learn

233
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:45,433
that the woman you love
is Amanda's daughter.

234
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:48,200
How can you let this happen,
Red?

235
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:51,033
Amanda killed your brother.

236
00:10:52,367 --> 00:10:54,533
Dad, she's not the one
who killed him.

237
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,833
What?

238
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,133
Is that your way of thinking?

239
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,167
Even if it wasn't her

240
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,933
who killed your brother
directly,

241
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:05,133
she's still the reason
why Angelo died.

242
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,067
She did a crime.

243
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:09,267
She was an accomplice.

244
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:14,600
But Yenyen has nothing to do
with what her mom did.

245
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:15,833
It doesn't matter.

246
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:20,000
If you love Eden, you'll have
to love her family too.

247
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:21,667
And how can you love Amanda?

248
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:26,300
You cannot love Eden
and hate Amanda

249
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:28,100
at the same time.

250
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:29,167
Wake up!

251
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,700
When I fell in love
with your mom,

252
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:35,133
I loved her whole family too.

253
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:42,267
So if you really care
about your mom, your family...

254
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:45,067
you will forget about Eden.

255
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,500
For our sake,

256
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:51,200
stay away from her.

257
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:58,333
But Eden is right.

258
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:01,633
She didn't mean to hurt you.

259
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:05,733
I mean, maybe it's their destiny
to meet on that island.

260
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:10,500
Of all people
that could fall in love,

261
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:14,533
why does it have to be
my daughter and Rina's son?

262
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,967
It's a small world.

263
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:23,600
And fate can be cruel sometimes.

264
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:25,333
You're right.

265
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,433
I'm so mad at my daughter.

266
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:32,567
I feel like she loves Red
more than she loves me!

267
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:36,533
She didn't even think
about how I would feel.

268
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,367
What are you talking about?

269
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:40,500
Eden loves you so much.

270
00:12:40,567 --> 00:12:43,100
Your daughter loves you so much.

271
00:12:43,167 --> 00:12:46,400
It's just too bad
that she fell in love

272
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:49,600
with the son
of your mortal enemy.

273
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:52,767
But think about her situation.

274
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:55,567
They're stranded on that island
alone.

275
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:57,567
They fell in love.

276
00:12:57,633 --> 00:13:00,433
They didn't know that
their parents hated each other.

277
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:12,533
How come you know a lot?

278
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,767
Did Eden tell you about him?

279
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,367
Do you know she's having
a relationship with Red?

280
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,700
You kept it from me, Dindi.

281
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:42,267
You know about their
relationship.

282
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:44,933
Amanda, sorry
for not telling you.

283
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,733
I know you'll get mad
if you find out.

284
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,667
You, too?

285
00:13:49,733 --> 00:13:52,367
You betrayed me too.

286
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:57,533
You let my daughter have
a relationship with that guy.

287
00:13:57,633 --> 00:13:58,700
Amanda...

288
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:01,033
I didn't know what to do.

289
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:02,267
I was caught
between a rock and a hard place.

290
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,300
If I had found out sooner,

291
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:05,433
I could have done something
about it.

292
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:08,067
But no, you condoned
her wrongdoing.

293
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:11,933
You didn't think about me.

294
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,733
Sorry.

295
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:19,600
You pushed my daughter
in harm's way.

296
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:22,267
Your own niece.

297
00:14:53,067 --> 00:14:54,933
Mom, can we talk.

298
00:14:59,967 --> 00:15:02,400
Please, talk to me.

299
00:15:06,367 --> 00:15:08,433
Mom, I'm sorry for hurting you.

300
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:14,567
I'm sorry for not telling you
about my relationship with Red.

301
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:17,733
I know what I did was wrong.

302
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,933
That's why I'm asking you
for forgiveness.

303
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:23,500
Mom, I'm sorry.

304
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:28,967
I'm sorry because I didn't think
about how you would feel.

305
00:15:31,367 --> 00:15:34,100
I regret everything, Mom.

306
00:15:35,967 --> 00:15:37,600
Mom, I'll do anything.

307
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:42,467
I'll do anything for you
to forgive me.

308
00:15:45,433 --> 00:15:46,700
Stay away from Red.

309
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:49,000
Forget him.

310
00:15:49,067 --> 00:15:51,300
Mom, I love him.

311
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:53,533
Then deal with the consequences.

312
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,533
I will never forgive
what you did.

313
00:15:58,233 --> 00:16:01,033
Forget that I'm your mom!

314
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,500
Mom, no!

315
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,067
Mom, I love you so much.

316
00:16:05,133 --> 00:16:08,033
Please don't make me choose.

317
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,333
If you love me,

318
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,433
then you have to obey me.

319
00:16:14,167 --> 00:16:17,067
Amanda, have pity on her.

320
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:18,067
Amanda, don't make her suffer.

321
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:19,600
You, too!

322
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:21,067
You two can stay together!

323
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,400
You're both liars!

324
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:23,767
Traitors!

325
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:24,900
Mom.

326
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:31,000
Eden, is your mom back yet?

327
00:17:31,067 --> 00:17:32,067
She's not here yet.

328
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:34,367
I've been waiting for her.

329
00:17:34,433 --> 00:17:35,800
Where did she go?

330
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:37,800
I have no idea.

331
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:42,000
It's all your fault.

332
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,500
Yes, you!

333
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:55,567
They made me suffer so much.

334
00:18:00,067 --> 00:18:04,367
How can you love
the son of my enemy?

335
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:09,000
She's mad at me.

336
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:11,000
She wants me to break up
with Red.

337
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:17,233
It's hard to let go
of the person I love.

338
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:25,067
People think I'm evil
because of their lies.

339
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,433
They ruined my life!

340
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:37,267
And now, you...

341
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:47,733
You're all I have left.

342
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:53,367
And you betrayed me.

343
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:58,200
Is that the right thing to do?

344
00:18:58,267 --> 00:19:00,367
Do I have to choose
between them?

345
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:04,800
To be honest,
you're in a tough spot.

346
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,400
Especially now, can you bear
seeing her like this?

347
00:19:07,467 --> 00:19:09,333
You don't even know
where she is right now.

348
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,367
If you want to be with him,
go ahead!

349
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:17,133
Leave!

350
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:19,067
You don't want to be with me?

351
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,767
I feel the same!

352
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:25,333
- Eden!
- Mom!

353
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,567
Amanda! What are you doing?

354
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:29,333
Are you drunk?

355
00:19:29,433 --> 00:19:30,433
- No, I'm not.
- Amanda!

356
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,100
- What are you doing?
- What are you doing?

357
00:19:33,167 --> 00:19:36,100
Let's go home. You're drunk!

358
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:38,067
My God! Come on, let's go home.

359
00:19:38,133 --> 00:19:39,867
- Mom...
- Amanda!

360
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,767
Why did you get yourself drunk?

361
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,067
Come on, let's go.

362
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:47,367
What's happening to your mom?

363
00:19:50,067 --> 00:19:51,067
How are you?

364
00:19:54,667 --> 00:19:56,733
I'm perfectly fine.

365
00:19:57,833 --> 00:19:58,800
Really?

366
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,033
Victor...

367
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:04,000
it was just an act.

368
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,333
It was not real.

369
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:08,933
I just did that to stop our son
from leaving.

370
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,033
Hello!

371
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:19,000
Rina, please don't do that
again.

372
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:20,467
You got me worried too.

373
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:23,033
Well, now that you know,
you don't have to worry anymore.

374
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:25,133
Okay? I'm just faking.

375
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,767
I had to be creative.

376
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:30,567
Okay, I understand.

377
00:20:30,633 --> 00:20:32,967
But next time,
give me a heads-up.

378
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,367
Okay, fine.

379
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,433
But come on, you have to admit.

380
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:37,667
I convinced him, right?

381
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:39,933
Look, he stayed here.

382
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,900
So you were faking it.

383
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:43,700
You weren't sick.

384
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:44,933
You lied to me.

385
00:20:46,633 --> 00:20:47,667
Red, wait. Wait!

386
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:48,633
Red!

387
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:04,233
Why did you get yourself drunk,
Amanda?

388
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:10,033
It's all my fault.

389
00:21:10,133 --> 00:21:13,767
She's being like this
because I hurt her feelings.

390
00:21:18,533 --> 00:21:19,933
Mom, get some rest.

391
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,133
I'll take care of you.

392
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,033
Just leave me alone.

393
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,433
Leave me alone.

394
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,533
My life is meaningless!

395
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:33,667
My own daughter betrayed me.

396
00:21:36,267 --> 00:21:38,633
I'm all alone now.

397
00:21:40,167 --> 00:21:41,867
I want to die.

398
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:46,600
No one loves me anymore.

399
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:48,900
Mom, that's not true.

400
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:51,000
You know I love you.

401
00:21:52,133 --> 00:21:55,400
Sorry for loving
the wrong person.

402
00:21:55,467 --> 00:21:59,200
But it doesn't mean
that I don't love you.

403
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:02,767
You're a liar!

404
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:06,433
Just leave!

405
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:09,033
You can go and be with your man.

406
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:12,100
If you're happy with him,

407
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:15,233
stay with him.

408
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,933
I won't stop you.

409
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:28,800
I hope they won't hurt you
as they hurt me.

410
00:22:28,867 --> 00:22:30,033
I hope...

411
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:40,333
I hope his family
will love you...

412
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:48,000
the way I do.

413
00:22:51,267 --> 00:22:52,567
Mom, I'm sorry.

414
00:22:58,033 --> 00:22:59,300
I'm sorry.

415
00:22:59,367 --> 00:23:01,867
I will never leave you.

416
00:23:03,867 --> 00:23:06,533
Mom, no one will ever love me
the way you do.

417
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:12,533
Mom, don't make me go away.

418
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:15,100
I'm sorry, Mom.

419
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:21,067
Mom, I love you so much.

420
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:25,200
I won't leave you.

421
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:28,400
I'll be sad without you.

422
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:32,100
Mom...

423
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:35,267
Mom, I need you.

424
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:54,067
Auntie, I think you really need
to know about something.

425
00:23:54,133 --> 00:23:54,967
About what?

426
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:56,600
It's about Red.

427
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:59,433
And what Eden's mom did to him.

428
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:01,033
Who would have thought

429
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:05,033
that his parents were the ones
that put you in jail?

430
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:07,033
I didn't betray you.

431
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:08,767
I just fell in love.

432
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:10,867
Who are you going to choose?

433
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:12,467
Me or Red?

434
00:24:12,533 --> 00:24:14,167
Miss Emma, where's my mom?

435
00:24:14,233 --> 00:24:16,500
She left with your Uncle Zandro.

436
00:24:16,567 --> 00:24:20,100
I heard they're going
to Eden's house.

437
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:21,833
I just scared him off

438
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:24,267
so he would leave my daughter
alone.

439
00:24:24,333 --> 00:24:26,100
You still threaten him.

440
00:24:26,167 --> 00:24:28,567
Perhaps you want me
to threaten your life too.

441
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:31,367
Show her what you're about
to throw in her house.
